# E2E test conventions

## Imports

Always import from `../fixtures/test`, never directly from `@playwright/test`:

```typescript
import { expect, test } from '../fixtures/test';
```

## Custom fixtures

- `manifest` — deterministic IDs/credentials from `E2eSeedService`. Never hardcode IDs.
- `loginAsCustomer(persona)` — authenticates as a customer persona via API + localStorage.
- `loginAsAdmin()` — authenticates as admin.
- `expectToast(title)` — asserts a toast notification appears.
- `waitForVisualReady()` — waits for network idle + fonts. Use before screenshots.

## Functional tests (`tests/e2e/functional/`)

- Use Page Objects from `page-objects/` for repeated UI flows.
- Prefer accessible locators: `getByRole`, `getByText`, `getByLabel`, `getByTestId`.
- Name files after features: `customer-dashboard.spec.ts`, `admin-course-management.spec.ts`.

## Visual tests (`tests/e2e/visual/`)

- Call `waitForVisualReady()` before every screenshot.
- Use: `await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('area/name.png', { fullPage: true })`.
- Snapshots committed in `tests/snapshots/`. Update with `npm run test:visual:update`.
- CI runs on Ubuntu — baselines generated on macOS will fail. Note snapshot updates in PRs.

## Adding test data

1. Add persona/entity in `backend/src/E2e/E2eSeedService.php`.
2. Extend `E2eManifest` type in `tests/e2e/fixtures/manifest.ts`.
3. Reference manifest values — never hardcode.

## ESLint

Same style as frontend: 4-space indent, single quotes, semicolons, explicit return types. Run `npm run lint` from `tests/`.
